SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (Agreement) is made and entered into this January 15, 2025 (the Effective Date), by and between EDPR Northeast Allen Solar Park LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Flatrock Creek Solar I), EDPR Northeast Allen Solar Park II LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Flatrock Creek Solar II), EDPR Northeast Allen Solar Park III LLC (Flatrock Creek Solar III), EDPR Northeast Allen Energy Storage Park LLC (Flatrock Creek Storage I) and EDPR Northeast Allen Energy Storage Park II LLC (Flatrock Creek Storage II). The foregoing are sometimes referred to herein individually as a Co-Owner and collectively as Co- Owners.
RECITALS
A. Flatrock Creek Solar I is developing a solar generation facility located in Allen County, Indiana commonly referred to as the Flatrock Creek I Solar Farm (the Flatrock Creek Solar I Facility).
B. Flatrock Creek Solar II is developing a solar generation facility located in Allen County, Indiana commonly referred to as the Flatrock Creek II Solar Farm (the Flatrock Creek Solar II Facility).
C. Flatrock Creek Solar III is developing a solar generation facility located in Allen County, Indiana commonly referred to as the Flatrock Creek III Solar Farm (the Flatrock Creek Solar III Facility).
D. Flatrock Creek Storage I is developing a battery energy storage facility located in Allen County, Indiana commonly referred to as the Flatrock Creek Storage I Battery Facility (the Flatrock Creek Storage I Facility).
E. Flatrock Creek Storage II is developing a battery energy storage facility located in Allen County, Indiana commonly referred to as the Flatrock Creek Storage I Battery Facility (the Flatrock Creek Storage II Facility); each of Flatrock Creek Solar I Facility, Flatrock Creek Solar II Facility, Flatrock Creek Solar III Facility, Flatrock Creek Storage I Facility, and Flatrock Creek Storage II Facility are referred to herein as a Facility and collectively as the Facilities). The Flatrock Creek Solar I Facility, Flatrock Creek Solar II Facility, Flatrock Creek Solar III Facility, Flatrock Creek Storage I Facility and Flatrock Creek Storage II Facility will be constructed adjacent to each other.
C. The installed nameplate generating capacity of each of the Facilities is as follows:
Flatrock Creek Solar I Facility: 100 MW Flatrock Creek Solar II Facility: 100 MW Flatrock Creek Solar III Facility: 100 MW Flatrock Creek Storage I Facility: 50 MW Flatrock Creek Storage II Facility: 50 MW

E. Flatrock Creek Solar I has designed and will construct and will have legal rights to operate and maintain the Shared Facilities (defined herein) with respect to the 345 kV transmission line to the point of interconnection at the Allen 345 kV Station and other associated facilities connecting the Flatrock Creek Solar I Facility to the transmission system.
F. Flatrock Creek Solar I holds certain real property interests subject to the easement, lease, option or other rights and obligations in the documents described under the applicable section of Exhibit B.
G. Subject to Section 4.1 herein, Flatrock Creek Solar II, Flatrock Creek Solar III, Flatrock Creek Storage I, and Flatrock Creek Storage II desire to acquire partial ownership rights in the Shared Assets and Shared Real Property (both as defined below), from Flatrock Creek Solar I to support the development and construction of the Flatrock Creek Solar II Facility, Flatrock Creek Solar III Facility, Flatrock Creek Storage I Facility, and Flatrock Creek Storage II Facility and to engage the Operator to operate, maintain, repair and manage the foregoing, all in accordance with and subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement.
NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the recitals, the premises, covenants and conditions contained herein, and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which the Co- Owners acknowledge, the Co-Owners agree as follows:
ARTICLE I -- DEFINITIONS, INTERPRETATIONS AND EXHIBITS
1.1 Definitions. As used in this Agreement, including the Recitals, and except as required by grammatical usage and apart from proper nouns, each capitalized term has the meaning given to it in this Agreement and in the Schedule of Definitions attached as Exhibit A.
1.2 Interpretation. In this Agreement, unless a clear, contrary intention appears: (a) the singular includes the plural and vice versa; (b) reference to any Person includes such Persons successors and assigns but, in the case of a Co-Owner, only if such assigns are permitted by this Agreement, and reference to a Person in a particular capacity excludes such Person in any other capacity; (c) reference to any gender includes each other gender; (d) reference to any agreement (including this Agreement), document or instrument means such agreement, document or instrument as amended, restated, supplemented or modified and in effect from time to time in accordance with the terms thereof and, if applicable, the terms of this Agreement; (e) reference to any Law means such Law as amended, modified, codified, or reenacted, in whole or in part, and in effect from time to time, including, if applicable, rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; (f) reference to any Section means such Section of this Agreement, and references in any Section or definition to any clause means such clause of such Section or definition; (g) hereunder, hereof, hereto and words of similar import shall be deemed references to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular Section or other provision of this Agreement; (h) including means including without limiting the generality of any description such term; and (i) relative to the determination of any period of time, from means from and including, to means to but excluding and through means through and including.

1.3 Incorporation of Recitals and Exhibits. The Recitals set forth in this Agreement and the Exhibits and Attachments attached hereto are incorporated into this Agreement by reference for all purposes.
ARTICLE II -- TERM OF AGREEMENT
2.1 Term. This Agreement shall become effective as of the Effective Date and shall remain in force and effect until the earlier of (a) the date that is fifty (50) years after the Effective Date; (b) the retirement and final disposition of all components of the Shared Facilities; (c) the date that Flatrock Creek Solar I terminates this Agreement pursuant to Section 4.1.3 herein and (d) the date that the Co-Owners unanimously agree to terminate this Agreement.
2.2 Payments on Termination. Upon termination of this Agreement, each Co-Owner shall pay Operator for its share, in proportion to its Undivided Use Interest at the time of such termination as set forth herein this Agreement, of any remaining balance owed for Operators costs incurred or irrevocably committed to be incurred pursuant to this Agreement as of the date of termination, within sixty (60) days following receipt of an invoice from Operator requiring such payment; provided that Operator shall use commercially reasonable efforts to minimize such costs.
2.3 Survival. Any obligations of one Co-Owner to another, including payment obligations and indemnity obligations, as a result of this Agreement which accrued prior to or as a result of termination of this Agreement shall survive termination of this Agreement.
ARTICLE III -- SHARED FACILITIES AND REAL PROPERTY
3.1 Shared Facilities. The Co-Owners plan to procure, install and construct, or have procured, installed and constructed, certain facilities for electrical transmission, communications¸ structures and other facilities, as described in Exhibit B, which may be altered or reconstructed by amendment in accordance with this Agreement, for shared use by the Co-Owners (collectively, the Shared Facilities). Each grouping of Shared Facilities is described in Exhibit B (each a Shared Facilities Group).
3.2 Shared Real Property. The Shared Facilities in each Shared Facilities Group are or will be located on certain real property (collectively, the Shared Real Property) that is subject to the easement, lease, option or other rights and obligations in the documents described under the applicable section of Exhibit B (collectively, the Shared Real Property Agreements).
3.3 Shared Assets Groups. Each Shared Facilities Group, combined with the Shared Real Property corresponding to the Shared Facilities in such Shared Facilities Group (Shared Assets) described under the same section in Exhibit B shall be referred to herein as a Shared Assets Group.
3.4 Access. Each Co-Owner shall have a non-exclusive right of access (a) to the Shared Facilities in which it has an Undivided Use Interest as necessary in order to ensure that Operator is meeting its obligations with respect to operation, maintenance and repair of such Shared Facilities, that Co-Owners Facility remains operational, and for the purposes contemplated in Article VII; (b) to make any necessary repairs to such Shared Facilities not timely made by Operator or in the event of an Emergency Condition; (c) to exercise any of its rights with respect to the Shared Facilities under this Agreement (including the inspection and testing rights under Section 5.2) and (d) over any Shared Real 3 Docusign Envelope ID: CCE4E812-44A3-4053-A1A9-6C59B6D6F970
Property in which such Co-Owner has an Ownership Interest; provided that, subject to the provisions of Section 13.1.4, if such Co-Owner is not the Operator, it shall (i) provide reasonable notice to Operator, and (ii) not unreasonably interfere with Operators operation, maintenance or repair of the Shared Facilities or of another Co-Owners Facility.
ARTICLE IV -- OWNERSHIP OF AND RIGHT TO USE SHARED ASSETS
4.1 Undivided Ownership Interests.
4.1.1 Notice to Acquire. In the event that Flatrock Creek Solar II, Flatrock Creek Solar III, Flatrock Creek Storage I, or Flatrock Creek Storage II (each an Acquiring Co-Owner) desires to proceed with the continued development and construction of the Flatrock Creek Solar II Facility, Flatrock Creek Solar III Facility, Flatrock Creek Storage I Facility, or Flatrock Creek Store II Facility, each Acquiring Co-Owner may, at its sole discretion, send a written notice to Flatrock Creek Solar I stating its desire to proceed with the consummation of the Ownership Interest Acquisition (as defined below) (the Notice to Acquire).
4.1.2 Ownership Interest Acquisition. Following Flatrock Creek Solar Is receipt of the Notice to Acquire, as soon as reasonably practical, (i) the Co-Owners shall (A) execute the Bill of Sale; (B) execute the Real Property Assignment and Assumption Agreement (as applicable) and the Warranty Deed (as applicable) and (C) amend this Agreement as reasonably required to accurately reflect the Shared Facilities; and (ii) Acquiring Co-Owner shall reimburse Flatrock Creek Solar I for the Capital Costs as set forth in Section 4.3 below (the Ownership Interest Acquisition), pursuant to which each Co-Owner shall own an undivided interest, as a tenant-in- common, in the applicable Shared Assets Group (and equal to its Proportionate Share as set forth and described in Exhibit C) (such undivided interest of each Co-Owner being referred to in this Agreement as its Ownership Interest). NOTWITHSTANDING ANYTHING HEREIN TO THE CONTRARY, FLATROCK CREEK SOLAR I SHALL HAVE NO LIABILITY TO ANY OTHER CO-OWNER FOR ANY DEFECT IN THE DESIGN, CONSTRUCTION OR UTILITY OF ANY OF THE SHARED FACILITIES. FLATROCK CREEK SOLAR I MAKES NO REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND WITH RESPECT TO THE CONDITION, USE OR FITNESS OF ANY OF THE SHARED REAL PROPERTY OR WITH RESPECT TO THE DESIGN, CONSTRUCTION, OPERATION OR UTILITY OF ANY OF THE SHARED FACILITIES AND HEREBY DISCLAIMS ANY WARRANTY OF MERCHANTABILITY OR FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE OR ANY OTHER WARRANTY OF ANY KIND WITH RESPECT TO THE SHARED REAL PROPERTY OR THE SHARED ASSETS. The Co-Owners agree they will look solely to the designers, contractors, suppliers, manufacturers and other Persons who participated in the design and/or construction of the Shared Facilities with respect to any defects or breaches of contract or warranty.
4.1.3 Acquiring Co-Owners Withdrawal Notice. Prior to the commencement of the Ownership Interest Acquisition, in the event that Acquiring Co-Owner desires to cease the development of the respective Acquiring Co-Owners Facility, at its sole discretion, Acquiring Co- Owner shall send written notice to Flatrock Creek Solar I of its decision to withdraw from this Agreement (the Withdrawal Notice). Upon Flatrock Creek Solar Is receipt of the Termination Notice, the respective Acquiring Co-Owner shall be removed from this Agreement, without 4 Docusign Envelope ID: CCE4E812-44A3-4053-A1A9-6C59B6D6F970
liability, subject only to any surviving obligations expressly provided hereunder. The delivery of a Withdrawal Notice by one Acquiring Co-Owner shall not cancel, void, or otherwise result in the termination of any rights of the other Acquiring Co-Owners. .
4.2 Undivided Use Interests. Each Co-Owner who has an Ownership Interest in a Shared Assets Group shall have an undivided right to the use or capacity of the applicable Shared Assets equal to its Proportionate Share set forth and described in Exhibit C, which right is exercisable upon the earlier of (i) the date of the consummation of the Ownership Interest Acquisition set forth in Section 4.1.2 herein and (ii) the Commissioning Date of its Facility by such Co-Owner providing written notice to the Operator and to the other Co-Owners in the same Shared Assets Group that the Commissioning Date has occurred, and provided that such Co-Owner has made the payment or payments set forth in Section 4.3, and that no Event of Default has occurred and is continuing with respect to such Co-Owner (once exercised, such undivided use interest of a Co-Owner is referred to in this Agreement as its Undivided Use Interest). Each Co-Owners Proportionate Share in its Shared Assets Group is set forth on Exhibit C, which may be revised from time to time in accordance with this Agreement.
4.2.1 Generator Lead Line. Each Co-Owner of a Generator Lead Line shall be entitled to use its Undivided Use Interest in the Delivery Capability of the Generator Lead Line. In the event that the Delivery Capability of the Generator Lead Line exceeds the capability provided in the applicable Interconnection Agreement, with Transmission Owners and Transmission Providers consent and approval, each Co-Owners Undivided Use Interest will be increased pro rata in accordance with its Ownership Interest for so long as the Delivery Capability is in excess of the capability provided in the Interconnection Agreements. For the avoidance of doubt, the Co-Owners will not exceed the Maximum Facility Output of the facility, as defined in the applicable Interconnection Agreement, unless all necessary approvals and consents are obtained (including from Transmission Owner and Transmission Provider).
4.2.2 Excess Capability. No Co-Owner shall have the right to use more than its Proportionate Share of the Delivery Capability of the Generator Lead Line or portion of the Generator Lead Line. During periods in which a Co-Owner is not utilizing its full Undivided Use Interest in the Delivery Capability of the Generator Lead Line or portion of Generator Lead Line, the other Co-Owners may utilize more than their full Undivided Use Interest, subject to the operating limits of the Shared Facilities, so long as such usage does not interfere with or adversely affect the first Co-Owners energy schedules and deliveries; and provided that (i) prior to any Co- Owner using more than its Proportionate Share of the Delivery Capability of the Generator Lead Line or portion of the Generator Lead Line, the Co-Owners shall have obtained all necessary Governmental Authorizations, including FERC acceptance for filing of an effective transmission services agreement for such usage to the extent required and (ii) no payment obligation will attach to such utilization by a Co-Owner of more than its full Undivided Use Interest.
4.3 Reimbursement of Capital Costs. On the consummation of the Ownership Interest Acquisition set forth in Section 4.1.2 herein, to compensate Flatrock Creek Solar I for having borne a disproportionate share of the costs and expenses of design, procurement, construction, installation and/or startup of the Shared Assets Group, Acquiring Co-Owner shall pay to Flatrock Creek Solar I an amount equal to (i) the Proportionate Share held by Acquiring Co-Owner set forth in Exhibit C, regardless of whether or not Acquiring Co-Owner has achieved its Commissioning Date) (ii) multiplied by the aggregate Capital Costs (such payment, the Reimbursement of Capital Costs). The Reimbursement 5 Docusign Envelope ID: CCE4E812-44A3-4053-A1A9-6C59B6D6F970
of Capital Costs shall be payable in U.S. dollars by wire transfer in immediately available funds to an account specified in writing by Flatrock Creek Solar I.
4.4 Additional Phases. Subject to the unanimous written consent of all of the Co-Owners, a Co-Owner or its Affiliate shall have the right to build and operate an additional phase or phases (an Additional Phase), to connect such Additional Phase (or such portion of the Additional Phase as may be compatible with Transmission Owners interconnection facilities), to the Shared Facilities and to use the Shared Assets, subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. Following the unanimous written consent of all of the Co-Owners, the owner of such Additional Phase shall execute a joinder, the form of which is attached as Exhibit H hereto (the Joinder), and the Co-Owners shall execute an appropriate amendment to this Agreement to reflect the Undivided Use Interest of the Additional Phase in the applicable Shared Assets Groups. Notwithstanding anything contained herein to the contrary, the owner of the Additional Phase shall bear any incremental costs and expenses of modifying and upgrading the applicable existing Shared Facilities to accommodate the connection of its Facility.
4.5 Initial Connection to Shared Facilities.
4.5.1 In connection with the initial interconnection of any Facility (a Connecting Facility) to any of the Shared Facilities, the Co-Owner that owns such Connecting Facility (the Connecting Co-Owner) shall be responsible for (and for all initial costs in respect of), the initial interconnection of such Connecting Facility to the Shared Facilities (the New Connection). Each Connecting Co-Owner acknowledges and agrees that the New Connection may result in (a) damage to the Shared Facilities or any other Co-Owners Facility; (b) claims from third parties and (c) lost revenues associated with scheduled and/or unscheduled outages and/or curtailment of some or all of the energy production from the New Connection of the Connecting Facility to any other Co-Owners Facility (including the cash value of any penalties imposed on the applicable Co-Owner or damages payable by the applicable Co-Owner to a power purchaser, energy hedge provider or transmission service provider for the applicable Co-Owners Facility) (together with related costs and/or expenses, collectively, New Connection Losses).
4.5.2 All New Connection Losses shall be the sole responsibility of the Connecting Co- Owner that owns the applicable Connecting Facility. As part of the process for implementation of any New Connection, the applicable Connecting Co-Owner shall establish a protocol to reasonably minimize disruptions to the Shared Facilities and any other Co-Owners Facility. Within ten (10) Business Days after receipt of written notice from the applicable Connecting Co-Owner that the applicable New Connection has been completed, each of the other Co-Owners shall reasonably determine its actual New Connection Losses and deliver reasonable backup documentation supporting the calculation thereof to the applicable the Connecting Co-Owner. Any dispute regarding the calculation of New Connection Losses shall be determined in accordance with the dispute resolution provisions in Exhibit D. The applicable Connecting Co-Owner shall pay to each other Co-Owner all undisputed New Connection Losses incurred by such Co- Owner within thirty (30) days following receipt of the calculation of New Connection Losses from such Co-Owner. Any disputed New Connection Losses incurred by any Co-Owner that are determined (in accordance with the dispute resolution provisions in Exhibit D), to be owed by the applicable Connecting Co-Owner shall be payable by such Connecting Co-Owner to such other Co-Owner within thirty (30) days following such determination. Each Co-Owner shall have all other rights and remedies as may be provided in this Agreement or otherwise available at law or in equity resulting from any Connecting Co-Owners failure to pay any New Connection Losses. 6 Docusign Envelope ID: CCE4E812-44A3-4053-A1A9-6C59B6D6F970
ARTICLE V -- METERING, MEASUREMENT OF ENERGY DELIVERIES AND LOSSES
5.1 Measurement of Energy and Allocation of Losses. Energy transmitted on the applicable Generator Lead Line shall be measured and allocated between the Co-Owners of the Shared Facilities as set forth on Attachment B-2 (the Revenue Metering Report and Diagram). The Revenue Metering Report and Diagram depicts and delineates several metering connections used to measure energy and allocate losses by and among the Facilities, and such metering calculations are used to determine the Facilities generated real power delivered to and received from the point of interconnect.
5.2 Testing and Repair of Co-Owners Meters.
5.2.1 Inspection and Testing. If applicable and in conformance with the applicable Interconnection Agreement(s), a Co-Owner will cause meters (other than revenue meters owned by the interconnection provider and check meters owned by the individual Co-Owner) to be inspected and tested upon its installation and at least once every twenty four (24) months thereafter, or more frequently if required by PJM rules, by the Interconnection Agreement or by any power purchase agreement to which a Co-Owner is a party, and at any other reasonable time upon the other Co-Owners request. The Co-Owner requesting such inspection and testing will pay the costs of same, unless the results of the test show the Co-Owners meter to be inaccurate by more than half of one percent (0.5%), in which case the Co-Owners will share the costs of the test. Each Co-Owner will give the other Co-Owners reasonable advance notice of tests of its meter and the other Co-Owners have the right to witness such tests.
5.2.2 Calibration or Repair. If a test shows a Co-Owners meter to be inaccurate, the owner or owners of the meter will use reasonable efforts to cause its meter to be calibrated, repaired or replaced as soon as reasonably practical. Such adjustments shall be reflected as charges or credits, as applicable, on the invoices for O&M Services rendered monthly by Operator to the Co-Owners.
5.3 Back-Feed Power. The Co-Owners will arrange for the provision of back-feed power service for each of their Facilities.
ARTICLE VI -- OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES.
6.1 Engagement of Operator. The Co-Owners hereby engage the Operator to manage, operate, maintain and repair the Shared Facilities and to perform other duties pertaining to the Shared Assets (the O&M Services), all as set forth in this Agreement. The Operator accepts such engagement and agrees to perform such duties in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof. Co-Owners acknowledge and agree that EDP Renewables North America LLC provides certain services with respect to the NERC Reliability Standards on their behalf and is the registered entity.
6.2 Standards for Operators Performance. Operator shall perform or cause to performed the O&M Services in accordance with Good Utility Practice, the Material Project Agreements, the Shared Real Property Agreements, this Agreement and all Applicable Laws and requirements of Governmental
7 Docusign Envelope ID: CCE4E812-44A3-4053-A1A9-6C59B6D6F970
Authorities, including without limitation all Hazardous Materials Laws and all Environmental Laws, and all safety policies and procedures (collectively, the Performance Standard).
6.3 O&M Services. The Operator shall provide or cause to be provided the following services on behalf of each of the Co-Owners who have an Undivided Use Interest from and after the date such Co-Owner has notified Operator of its exercised right to an Undivided Use Interest in the Shared Assets pursuant to Section 4.2 (the O&M Services Commencement Date):
(a) manage, supervise, operate, repair and maintain the Shared Assets, including the day to day management of the Shared Assets in accordance with Material Project Agreements¸ Good Utility Practice and the Annual O&M Budget;
(b) pay and collect amounts due in connection with the Shared Assets including but not limited to taxes and assessments pursuant to Section 12.2, and maintain one or more bank accounts wherein funds received by the Operator in connection with its duties herein shall be maintained;
(c) expend monies necessary for the management, operation, maintenance and repair of the Shared Facilities;
(d) notify every Co-Owner of any notice (or any other information reasonably anticipated to affect the Co-Owners) received by the Operator or received from any Co-Owner;
(e) manage compliance with the Co-Owners rights in Shared Real Property in accordance with the Shared Real Property Agreements, including making payments required thereunder; provided that the Operator shall have no right to amend such rights in the Shared Real Property; and
(f) with respect to the Shared Real Property and the Shared Facilities located on the Shared Real Property, oversee all investigations, studies, clean up, corrective action or response or remedial action required by any Governmental Authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters or by any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to the use, operation or ownership of the Shared Real Property or the Shared Facilities locate on the Shared Real Property.
6.4 Scheduled Maintenance. Operator shall schedule, or cause to be scheduled, maintenance and any planned outages of the Shared Facilities so as to minimize interference with Co-Owners scheduled energy deliveries. Maintenance and any planned outages of the Shared Facilities shall be scheduled, to the maximum extent possible, during scheduled maintenance outages of the Co-Owners Facilities. Each Co-Owner will provide to the Operator and the other affected Co-Owners by January 1 of each year a schedule of planned maintenance outages on such Co-Owners Facility for the subsequent twelve- month period. Scheduled outages of the Shared Facilities will be subject to the mutual approval by the affected Co-Owners, such approval not to be unreasonably withheld. Operator will seek to limit the duration of any outage, planned or unplanned, consistent with the Performance Standard.
6.5 Unplanned Outages. Operator will notify, or cause to be notified, Co-Owners of all emergency or unplanned outages of any of the Shared Facilities as soon as practicable, in accordance 8 Docusign Envelope ID: CCE4E812-44A3-4053-A1A9-6C59B6D6F970
with Good Utility Practice, and will provide an estimated time of return of the Shared Facilities to service, or if not known, will keep, or cause to be kept, Co-Owners advised regarding the status of same.
6.6 Emergency Conditions. In the event of an emergency condition involving the Shared Assets that could be reasonably expected by Operator to result in possible personal injury, loss of life, damage to or destruction of property, or danger to the public (an Emergency Condition), the Operator shall, without the need for prior notification of the Co-Owners, take such action, or cause such action, as may be reasonable and necessary, as determined in the sole discretion of the Operator, to prevent, avoid or mitigate such loss, and shall, as soon as reasonably practicable, report any such emergency, including the Operators response thereto, to the Co-Owners, and Operator, if allowed by law, be compensated by the Co-Owners for the costs of taking such actions in proportion to their Ownership Interest in the Shared Assets so affected.
6.7 O&M Costs. Costs of performing O&M Services (the O&M Costs) shall be budgeted accordingly and include all payments made and expenses incurred by Operator in performing O&M Services (at cost and without markup), including but not limited to related overhead and applicable taxes, and costs (except insurance costs) related to ownership of the Shared Assets.
6.8 Budgeting Process. Each year during the term of this Agreement, Operator will prepare a forecast budget of O&M Costs for the following calendar year and will provide a copy to Co-Owners by December 1st. Co-Owners will have thirty (30) days thereafter to review the forecast budget and discuss any concerns with the forecast budget with Operator, provided that following the 30-day period such forecast budget of O&M Costs shall be deemed approved if no concerns are identified in writing by the Co-Owners. Operators implementation of the O&M Services consistent with the forecast budget is subject to Co-Owners prior approval, not to be unreasonably withheld (such approved forecast budget, the Annual O&M Budget). The Annual O&M Budget shall include allocated costs and expenses to each Shared Assets Group to the extent reasonably practical.
6.9 Extraordinary Maintenance. Each Co-Owner agrees to reimburse Operator for its share, in proportion to its Undivided Use Interest, of the costs of any maintenance or other services required in the event of unusual or catastrophic circumstances, to the extent such costs were not included in the forecast budget for O&M Services and incurred by the Operator (Extraordinary Maintenance).
6.10 Responsibility for O&M Costs.
(a) Each Co-Owner shall be responsible for its share, in proportion to its Undivided Use Interest, of O&M Costs, including its share of the costs of any Extraordinary Maintenance incurred by Operator, which shall be invoiced by Operator on a quarterly basis. On or before the tenth (10th) day following the end of each calendar quarter, Operator shall invoice Co-Owners for their respective Undivided Use Interest of 1/4 of the amount of the current Annual O&M Budget, along with the costs of any Extraordinary Maintenance performed in the previous quarter. The invoices shall be delivered to the parties identified in Section 17.15. Co-Owners shall pay such invoice within thirty (30) days of its receipt (the Due Date). Any amounts not paid by the Due Date shall be deemed delinquent and shall accrue interest at the then-effective prime rate of interest published under Money Rates by The Wall Street Journal, plus two percent per annum from the Due Date to the date of payment (the Late Payment Rate). For purposes of this Section 6.10 and for Section 6.11, receipt shall mean the date upon which the invoice is received 9 Docusign Envelope ID: CCE4E812-44A3-4053-A1A9-6C59B6D6F970
in accordance with Section 17.15. In the event that any Due Date falls upon a weekend day or bank holiday, such payment shall be due and payable on the first Business Day immediately thereafter.
(b) Within sixty (60) days after the end of each calendar year, Operator shall invoice the Co- Owners for, or shall refund to the Co-Owners, as applicable, their Proportionate Shares of the difference between the sum of the Annual O&M Budget and the costs of any Extraordinary Maintenance and the actual amount of O&M Costs paid or incurred in such calendar year. Any invoice for such amounts shall be paid within the Due Date. The invoices shall be delivered to Co-Owners as set forth in Section 17.15. Any amounts not paid when due shall be deemed delinquent and shall accrue interest at the Late Payment Rate. In the event that any due date falls upon a weekend day or bank holiday, such payment shall be due and payable on the first Business Day immediately thereafter.
6.11 Disputes. If a Co-Owner disputes the accuracy of all or any portion of an invoice, such Co-Owner shall, nevertheless, pay the undisputed portion of the amount owing on the invoice and submit to Operator a written statement detailing the items and amount disputed. If Co-Owner and Operator are unable to resolve the disputed items, the matter will be resolved in accordance with the dispute resolution provisions in Exhibit D.
